# StageConnect - React + Laravel Project Rules

## Project Type
This is a Single Page Application (SPA) with:
- Frontend: React 19 + React Router + Tailwind CSS 4.0
- Backend: Laravel 12 API
- Build Tool: Vite

## File Structure Rules

### Frontend (React)
- All React components go in `resources/js/`
- Page components: `resources/js/pages/*.jsx`
- Reusable components: `resources/js/components/*.jsx`
- Use functional components with hooks only
- Use JSX syntax (.jsx extension)

### Backend (Laravel)
- API controllers: `app/Http/Controllers/Api/*.php`
- API routes: `routes/api.php`
- All API routes are prefixed with `/api`
- Return JSON responses from controllers

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow dark mode support pattern (light/dark variants)
- Color scheme: #1b1b18 (dark), #EDEDEC (light text), #f53003 (accent)

## Coding Standards

### React
```jsx
// ✅ Good - Functional component with hooks
export default function MyComponent() {
    const [state, setState] = useState(null);
    
    useEffect(() => {
        // Side effects
    }, []);
    
    return <div>Content</div>;
}

// ❌ Bad - Class components
class MyComponent extends React.Component { }
```

### Laravel API
```php
// ✅ Good - Return JSON
public function index()
{
    return response()->json([
        'data' => $data
    ]);
}

// ❌ Bad - Return views from API
public function index()
{
    return view('page');
}
```

## Naming Conventions

### Files
- React components: PascalCase (e.g., `MyComponent.jsx`)
- Laravel controllers: PascalCase (e.g., `MyController.php`)
- Routes: kebab-case (e.g., `/api/my-endpoint`)

### Code
- React: camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components
- Laravel: camelCase for methods, snake_case for database

## Import Rules

### React
```jsx
// External packages first
import { useState } from 'react';
import { Link } from 'react-router-dom';

// Components next
import MyComponent from '../components/MyComponent';

// Styles last (if any)
import './styles.css';
```

### Laravel
```php
// Framework imports
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

// App imports
use App\Models\MyModel;
use App\Http\Controllers\Controller;
```

## API Communication

### Frontend → Backend
- Use `fetch()` or `axios` for API calls
- All API endpoints start with `/api/`
- Handle loading states
- Handle errors gracefully

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/endpoint')
        .then(res => res.json())
        .then(data => setData(data))
        .catch(err => console.error(err));
}, []);
```

## Routing Rules

### React Router (Frontend)
- Define routes in `App.jsx`
- Use `<Link>` for navigation (not `<a>`)
- All routes are client-side (no page reload)

### Laravel (Backend)
- API routes in `routes/api.php`
- SPA fallback in `routes/web.php` (must be last)
- No blade views except `app.blade.php`

## Build Commands

### Development
- `composer dev` - Start all servers
- `npm run dev` - Vite only
- `php artisan serve` - Laravel only

### Production
- `npm run build` - Build React app
- `php artisan optimize` - Optimize Laravel

## Testing
- React: Add tests in `resources/js/__tests__/`
- Laravel: Add tests in `tests/Feature/Api/`

## Don't Do This
❌ Mix blade views with React
❌ Use class components in React
❌ Return HTML from API endpoints
❌ Put business logic in React components
❌ Skip error handling in API calls
❌ Forget to handle loading states

## Always Do This
✅ Separate concerns (UI in React, logic in Laravel)
✅ Use TypeScript types if added
✅ Handle loading and error states
✅ Use semantic HTML
✅ Follow accessibility best practices
✅ Keep components small and focused
✅ Use environment variables for config

